	<h2>Buttons</h2>
	<p>
		Native button elements will be styled automatically.
		If wanting to make a link or span look like a button use the <code>.button</code> class.
	</p>
	<p>
		There is also the <code>.loud</code> class to indicate importance, and the <code>.attn</code>
		class to grab the users attention. (The attn class should be limited to one per visual screen.)
	</p>
	<p>
		Use a <code>&lt;span></code> inside a <code>&lt;button></code> element to keep Internet Explorer
		from shifting the text when pressing the button. Note: this cannot be avoided for input type buttons
		and does not occur on link buttons.
	</p>
	<div class="card">

		<div class="outline example">
			<input type="button" value="Standard button" />
			<button class="loud"><span>Loud button</span></button>
			<a href="#" class="button attn">Attn button</a>
		</div>
		<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;input type="button" value="Standard button" />
&lt;button class="loud">&lt;span>Loud button&lt;/span>&lt;/button>
&lt;a href="#" class="button attn">Attn button&lt;/a>	
</pre>
	</div>

	<h3>Flat Buttons</h3>
	<p>
		Add a <code>.flat</code> class name for buttons already on a raised content area or an area.
	</p>
	<div class="card">
		<div class="outline example">
			<input type="button" class="flat" value="Standard button" />
			<button class="flat loud"><span>Loud button</span></button>
			<a href="#" class="flat button attn">Attn button</a>
		</div>
		<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;input type="button" class="flat" value="Standard button" />
&lt;button class="flat loud">&lt;span>Loud button&lt;/span>&lt;/button>
&lt;a href="#" class="flat button attn">Attn button&lt;/a>	
</pre>

	</div>

	<h3>Disabled Buttons</h3>
	<p>
		All buttons will style accordingly when adding the <code>[disabled]</code> attribute.
	</p>
	<div class="card">
		<div class="outline example">
			<input type="button" value="Standard disabled" disabled />
			<button class="loud" disabled><span>Loud disabled</span></button>
			<a class="button attn" disabled>Attn disabled</a>
			<input type="button" class="flat" value="Standard disabled" disabled />
			<button class="flat loud" disabled><span>Loud disabled</span></button>
			<a class="flat button attn" disabled>Attn disabled</a>
		</div>
		<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;input type="button" value="Standard disabled" disabled />
&lt;button class="loud" disabled>&lt;span>Loud disabled&lt;/span>&lt;/button>
&lt;a class="button attn" disabled>Attn disabled&lt;/a>
&lt;input type="button" class="flat" value="Standard disabled" disabled />
&lt;button class="flat loud" disabled>&lt;span>Loud disabled&lt;/span>&lt;/button>
&lt;a class="flat button attn" disabled>Attn disabled&lt;/a>
</pre>
	</div>
		


