	<h2>Additional Form Styling</h2>

	<h3>Errors</h3>
	<p>To draw attention to a field add a <code>.error</code> class name on the <code>.form-field</code> div.</p>
	<p>An <code>.alert</code> div can be used for general form errors. h1 - h4 headings can be used (and all style the same way).</p>
	<div class="card">

		<div class="outline example">
			<form class="error">
				<div class="alert-error"><h1>There was an error</h1>This is a general form alert.</div>
				<fieldset>
					<legend>Legend</legend>
					<div class="form-field error">
						<label for="text1">Label name</label>
						<input type="text" id="text1" placeholder="Type something…">
						<span data-validation-for="text1">Example block-level help in a span.</span>
					</div>
				</fieldset>
			</form>
		</div>
		<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;form class="error">
	&lt;div class="alert-error">&lt;h1>There was an error.&lt;/h1>This is a general form alert.&lt;/div>
	&lt;fieldset>
		&lt;legend>Legend&lt;/legend>
		&lt;div class="form-field error">
			&lt;label for="text1">Label name&lt;/label>
			&lt;input type="text" id="text1" placeholder="Type something…">
			&lt;span data-validation-for="text1">Example block-level help in a span.&lt;/span>
		&lt;/div>
	&lt;/fieldset>
&lt;/form>
</pre>
	</div>


	<h3>Disabled Fields</h3>
	<p>Simple use the <code>[disabled]</code> attribute on any item to disable it.</p>
	<div class="card">
		<div class="outline example">
			<label disabled>Disabled label</label>
			<input type="text" disabled value="This is a disabled field" />
			<input type="button" disabled valuie="Disabled button" value="Go" />
		</div>
		<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;label disabled>Disabled label&lt;/label>
&lt;input type="text" disabled value="This is a disabled field" />
&lt;input type="button" disabled valuie="Disabled button" />	
</pre>
	</div>

	<h3>Input Impersonator</h3>
	<p>The <code>.input</code> class will attempt to make any element look like an input field.</p>
	<div class="card">
		<div class="outline example">
			<input type="text" value="This is a normal text input" />
			<a href="#" class="input">This is a link that looks like an input</a>
		</div>
		<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;a href="#" class="input">This is a link that looks like an input&lt;/a>
</pre>
	</div>
</div>




